title: Service Creation
id: a9fbf537-0646-483f-a9d8-8d94f65abb26
status: experimental
description: Detects service modification via Set Value in "\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\". This detection is pertinent if service creation occurred in memory and command-line arguments were not logged.
references:
  - https://support.scythe.io/knowledge/march-2024-ioc-applejeus
author: Tyler Casey @1qazCasey, @scythe_io
date: 2024-03-13
tags:
  - attack.persistence
  - attack.t1050
logsource:
  product: windows
  category: registry_set
detection:
  selection_img:
    Image|endswith:
      - '\services.exe'
  selection_targetobj:
    TargetObject|contains:
      - '\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\'
  selection_allowlist: # Add known good services here to reduce FP
    TargetObject|contains: 
      - '\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\WinDefend'
  condition: selection_img and selection_targetobj and not selection_allowlist
falsepositives:
  - Legitimate administrator or user creates a service for legitimate reasons. Add known good services to selection_allowlist to be excluded.
level: medium
